# Software Requirements Specification (SRS)

# Assignment Management System

Version: 1.0
Prepared By: Development Team
Date: July 2026

---

# 1. Introduction

## 1.1 Purpose

The purpose of this project is to develop a centralized web-based Assignment Management System that simplifies assignment creation, submission, evaluation, communication, and reporting for students and faculty while providing complete administrative control and analytics.

The system aims to replace manual assignment tracking and fragmented communication with a secure and scalable platform.

---

## 1.2 Scope

The system will provide:

* Assignment creation and management for faculty.
* Assignment submission and tracking for students.
* Team assignment support.
* Approval and rejection workflow.
* Late submission handling.
* Real-time communication between faculty and students.
* Administrative analytics and monitoring.
* File preview and export capabilities.
* Role-based access control.

The platform is designed to support multiple branches, sections, subjects, and semesters.

